import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data, legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Count', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    
    data_grouped = data.groupby(data['time'].dt.to_period('M')).mean().reset_index()
    data_grouped['time'] = data_grouped['time'].dt.to_timestamp()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='time', y='count', data=data_grouped)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average count per time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time Period')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    
    avg_count = data_grouped['count'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Count: {avg_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of count?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='count', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the maximum and minimum count?", wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['count'].min():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['count'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['count'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
